.TH "rvt_mcast_find" 9 "rvt_mcast_find" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_mcast_find \- search the global table for the given multicast GID/LID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rvt_mcast *" rvt_mcast_find
.BI "(struct rvt_ibport *ibp "  ","
.BI "union ib_gid *mgid "  ","
.BI "u16 lid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ibp" 12
the IB port structure
.IP "mgid" 12
the multicast GID to search for
.IP "lid" 12
the multicast LID portion of the multicast address (host order)
.SH "NOTE"
It is valid to have 1 MLID with multiple MGIDs.  It is not valid
to have 1 MGID with multiple MLIDs.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The caller is responsible for decrementing the reference count if found.
.SH "RETURN"
NULL if not found.
